This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image synthesis. It also involves the use of deep learning architecture, which makes it likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of custom loss function suggests that it may belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the focus on medical image synthesis makes it likely to belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
